  <walkingDescription><![CDATA[<p>Bad Kleinkirchheim, the Nockberge region and the National Park all offer a comprehensive network of footpaths and plenty of opportunities for exercise. The well-marked hiking paths guide you through breath-taking and inspiring landscape.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span>SUMMER CABLE CARS OPENING SUMMER 2019</span></strong></p>
<p>Two cable-cars operate in summer in the BKK/St. Oswald region:</p>
<ul>
<li>The National Park lift, Brunnach, runs from approx. 26 May until 9 Sep daily, from 12 Sep until late September from Wednesdays to Saturdays.</li>
<li>The Kaiserburg lift runs daily from approx. 26 June until 12 September, Saturday to Tuesday from 15th Sep until late September.</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Speik Walks:</strong> On selected hiking trails you can enjoy the fresh and aromatic scent of the alpine valerian plant the region is famous for - the Speik. Particularly intense in July and August, it is considered to be both stimulating and harmonising at the same time. In eleven rustic alpine huts you’ll find Speik footbath and free massage oil from Speick Natural Cosmetics:</li>
<ul>
<li>Buschenschank Matl-Sepp – Speikstatue</li>
<li>Bad Kleinkirchheimer Wolitzenhütte</li>
<li>Bergrestaurant Kaiserburg</li>
<li>Brentlerhütte/Nockalm-Priedhof</li>
<li>Brunnachhof/St. Oswald</li>
<li>Buschenschank Hübelbauer</li>
<li>Buschenschank Streitnighof</li>
<li>Falkerthaus</li>
<li>Lärchenhütte/St. Oswald</li>
<li>St. Oswalder Bockhütte</li>
<li>Feriendorf Kirchleitn</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<p>Popular walks include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>The Discovery Tour</strong> / 5-6hrs / 600m altitude / 12km / Moderate: This circular walk of the BKK/St Oswald region starts off in the centre of BKK. Head towards the Römerbad Thermal Spa, passing the golf course and the speik sculpture, from where you can enjoy beautiful panoramic views of the extended Kirchheim valley. There you could also purchase alpine valerian products or enjoy an alpine valerian treatment. The walk continues towards St Oswald to the Weger Stadl museum. From there you can either walk back to BKK or get on the free walkers' bus.</li>
<li><strong>The Falkert </strong> / 6hrs / 940m altitude / 11km / Moderate: Take the free walkers bus to St Oswald and get off at the Alte Schmiede craft museum. The path initially leads along a road to the Falkerthaus. Following the scent of the alpine valerian, which is particularly noticeable in July and August. Take path #11 which leads you towards the Lärchen hut where you could stop for a refreshment. From there the route climbs up to the Hundsfeldscharte. Once here, follow path 109 on to the Falkert mountain (2,308m). Path #12 takes you back to St Oswald.</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>The Alpe Adria Trail - Hiking in the Garden of Eden</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Connects</strong> the three countries/regions of Carinthia-Austria, Slovenia and Friuli Venezia Giulia-Italy in 43 stages</li>
<li><strong>Long distance hiking trail</strong> leading from the foot of the highest mountain in Austria, the Grossglockner, through the most beautiful lakes and mountain regions in Carinthia to the Adriatic coast</li>
<li><strong><strong>Stage 16 </strong>Falkerthaus/Lärchenhütte - Bad Kleinkirchheim</strong></li>
<ul>
<li><strong class="s5">Difficulty: </strong><span class="abstractDifficulty d3">difficult</span></li>
<li><strong class="s5">Distance: </strong>19.2 km</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Ascent: </strong>1262 m</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Descent: </strong>1805 m</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Duration: </strong>8:00 h</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Lowest point: </strong>1022 m</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Highest point: </strong>2308 m</li>
</ul>
<li><strong><strong>Stage 17</strong> Bad Kleinkirchheim - Arriach</strong></li>
<ul>
<li><strong class="s5">Difficulty: </strong><span class="abstractDifficulty d2">moderate</span></li>
<li><strong class="s5">Distance: </strong>17.6 km</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Ascent: </strong>1258 m</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Descent: </strong>1405 m</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Duration: </strong>7:00 h</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Lowest point: </strong>869 m</li>
<li><strong class="s5">Highest point: </strong>2132 m</li>
</ul>
</ul>]]></walkingDescription>
